gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 123, Spurs 87
gameRecap.excerpt: The Thunder defeated the Spurs, 123-87, and improve to 7-4 on the season. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander led the Thunder with 28 points, six rebounds, five assists, and a career-high seven steals as Josh Giddey added 18 points, seven assists, and seven rebounds. Julian Champagnie led the Spurs with 13 points as Victor Wembanyama added eight points, 14 rebounds, and two blocks. The Spurs move to 3-8 on the year. The Thunder move to 1-2 as the Spurs fall to 0-2 in West: Group C play.
